          "cards": null,
          "body": "Find answers to the most common questions entrepreneurs ask when planning, launching, and managing a new vending machine route or office service.",
          "title": "Starting a Vending Machine Business: FAQ",
          "ctaHref": null,
          "bulletItems": null,
          "blockType": "faq",
          "ctaLabel": null,
          "faqItems": [
            {
              "answer": "Initial costs typically include purchasing or leasing the vending machines, securing initial inventory, and obtaining business licenses. Depending on whether you choose new, refurbished, or smart electronic coffee machines, starting expenses can vary. It is practical to outline a budget covering delivery, installation, and early stock before launch.",
              "question": "What are the typical startup costs for a vending machine business?"
            },
            {
              "question": "How do I secure high-traffic locations like offices?",
              "answer": "Securing locations—such as corporate offices, waiting rooms, or logistics hubs—involves reaching out to property or facility managers. Successful operators present a clean proposal detailing how the service benefits staff, the product range, and how maintenance or restocking is managed without hassle."
            },
            {
              "answer": "Most areas require a standard business license and potentially health department permits, especially when serving warm beverages like coffee. General liability insurance is highly recommended to cover the machines, location assets, and any product-related incidents.",
              "question": "What licensing and insurance do I need to get started?"
            },
            {
              "question": "How often do vending machines require maintenance and restocking?",
              "answer": "Servicing frequency depends on location volume. Busy offices might need restocking and basic cleaning multiple times a week, while quieter sites may only require weekly visits. Many modern machines offer remote telemetry so you can monitor inventory levels from your phone and plan efficient routes."
            }
          ]
        }
      }
